{
  "texts": [
    "Previous research showed that a lower temperature value may be preferable for text annotation tasks, as it seems to increase consistency without decreasing accuracy [13].",
    "Here, we extend the previous research results by assessing the effect of a lower temperature in LLaMA-1 (HuggingChat).",
    "Similar to [13], we set the temperature at its default value and 0.2 and compare the outputs with respect to accuracy and intercoder agreement.",
    "We conducted two sets of annotations for each temperature value to compute LLM's intercoder agreement.Our results demonstrate that lower temperature settings significantly enhance intercoder agreement, underscoring the deterministic and repeatable nature of the annotations.",
    "For instance, GPT -3.5's average intercoder agreement increased from 91.7% to 97.6% when the temperature was reduced from 1 to 0.2 in the zero-shot setting and from 92.3% to 95.4% in the few-shot setting."
  ]
}